<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>Hyperlinks</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Hyperlinks in HTML are created using the <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> tag with the gref attribute to specify the link destinction. The target attribute determines how the link is Opened.</p>
        <h1>Basic Hyperlink</h1>
        <p>Visit the <a href="https://www.google.co.in/" target="_self">Google</a> website.(Open in the same tab)</p>
        <h1>Open Link in New Tab</h1>
        <p>Visit the <a href="https://www.wikipedia.org/" target="_blank">Wikipedia</a> website.(Open in a new tab)</p>
        <h1>Open Link in Parent Frame</h1>
        <p>If this page is inside a frame, visit <a href="https://www.example.com" target="_parent">Example</a> in the parent frame</p>
        <h1>Open Link in Full Window</h1>
        <p>Visit <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news" target="_top">BBC News</a> to load in the full browser window.</p>
    </body>
</html>
